social_posts.post_text: Happy Birthday @firsthoneynz Burn Salve! A year around the sun and now around the world 🐝 🕊️ 🎉
Summer pile up. My inbox is in a similar state 🫣😆

Summer storms 📷 @lightbyiris Nothing quite like them to remind you change will come when we least expect it! Been a melancholy day farewelling visiting NZ family and preparing for a big work week so the weather seems fitting. My Nan used to tell me “You can’t calm a storm so stop trying. What you can do is calm yourself. The storm will pass. “  life lessons from the weather ⛈️🕊️

My little tub of foot rescue ☺️ Might be one of my favorite products we’ve made : ) I knew it was good when I’d used every formulation sample, including some extra ‘test runs’ for myself and was desperately waiting for production to get my hands on more lol. Thankfully I have a good supply now which is saving my heels in these crazy hot summer days.  It will be having a little upgrade soon in the packaging department and with some supporting ‘tools’ but that original formulation will stay solid! 💛 🐝

Picture of a working mother making lemons out of lemonade while simultaneously being perfectly on brand 😜 🍋 In reality I’m digging deep at the moment to make all the things work in the beautiful carnage that is summer. But the smile is real, and I’ve been thinking a lot lately about Mel Robbins' work on the ‘high five’ -  based on the concept that it’s neurologically impossible to criticize yourself while you are mentally high-fiving yourself. It actually creates positive programming in your brain… 
 
Perhaps there is room for a little more high fiving in life. And lemonade ; ) 🕊️ 🍋 🙌

Dream team. These humans bring so much good energy into the world and I’m very thankful for them. In the words of the great Leslie Knope “Go find your team. Get to work. Whatever that work is that you find worth doing. Do it, and find some people to love who'll do it with you.” 🐝💕
July things. The days feeling lately like they melt together under the heat and sweet sticky chaos that is summer 🍦🌞🐝🕊️

Work. July edition. 
 
No better picture to sum up my working life, especially this summer!  Laptop in hand, kiddos racing around my feet in various states of clothing. Long suffering teammate dictating notes while dodging pillows to the head 😬😝
 
I am often found apologizing for our ‘carnage’. But lately I’ve been far better at telling people up front this is my life and if you want to be a part of it buckle up for the ride!  It’s hard and perhaps unconventional at times but we’ve found our own rhythm and thankfully people who will work to the same beat. I love that we do so much of it together as a family, that the kids have such a high level of ownership and understanding even of what we are building. 
 
All that being said, on this final day of July I will admit a small sigh of relief that school is around the corner.  😅📚✏️

Sunday favorites 🌧️👧👦🧒

The best legacy we leave is not for our children but IN them…

Been thinking so much about this lately, as we start a new school year. The world is groaning, our impact on the environment and responsibility to protect and restore what is hurting feels so great. But change comes from people who have eyes to see ahead, sacrifice for a greater good and fight for what is right. Perhaps the most important thing of all then is to really steward our children's hearts, bring them into the conversation. Bring them into the fight. Show them the battle ahead because it is theirs to fight too. 

🌱 🌏 🐝

Labor day follow up. I have decided short weeks really just become an exercise in how to cram 5 working days into 4. 😜

Bundled the twins up for a quick work trip to Seattle for Amazon Accelerate. Amazon has become a significant part of our business over the past few years. Accessibility to products in the First Aid category is vital, and it’s been really amazing to meet with other sellers and build relationships with the wider Amazon team as we grow.  They have such great support for Female owned businesses, and I’m reminded again as I juggle calls to NZ, croupy children and honestly a good deal of PMS how important that is! Thankful for the amazing females in all capacities that are making our journey, story and world work this week! X

Quick work trip downtown and down memory lane remembering our early days in Nashville. We had a kiwi friend who used to call this building the “One Eyed Great Dane”. I think most locals call it the Batman Building. Kind of crazy thinking about how many feet and journeys have passed underneath the shadow of its ears. Excited to head into a new chapter with First Honey soon under the watchful gaze of whatever it is up there!
Homecoming. Foreign concept to us as kiwis so it’s been a week of firsts, fun and sweet friends helping us navigate all the things 🥰
Remedy for a fast paced life. All the super slow little things 💛🕊️
Caught snacking on set again, but at least it’s on brand! Another great day shooting with @smallhandscreative for @firsthoneynz

Early morning messages and videos from Dan, hive moving has begun and another harvest season approaches in New Zealand. Got me reminiscing on this year, the work that has been done and what is to come. The preparation to build towards each harvest and each product release is so intense.  As leaves here in Nashville fall, and buds start sprouting across the world in New Zealand it strikes me again how interconnected we all are, and the responsibility we have for each other. To grow, nurture and build the best world we can together.

Pumpkin decorating competition at school. I have low expectations for engagement on most things with Nova but more and more she is wanting in on all the action. She told me she was going to make a mermaid princess pumpkin, so I rolled with it. She won first place for her grade and “almost cried happy tears” 🥹 I have no idea what our future holds and I’m under no illusion that it’s going to suddenly get easy. Sometimes my fears for her future feel overwhelming, but then moments like this will sneak up and remind me there will be plenty of happy tears in our future. Just have to keep our hearts and hands open. Our pumpkins and path may look different but we will find our way 💕🎃 

#autismgirls #autismawareness #autismfamily
Better watch out its Halloween night 🎃👻

Just got a call from school to say my little guy had fallen on the playground. He is fine, they cleaned and bandaged him up and were just letting me know he was ok. The complete contrast to all the mothers, sons, daughters right now facing such horrific suffering with no sweet call or easy fix. So many people are hurting, I wish I could bandage up all the pain. It can feel impossible to breathe with the reality of it. 

The only place I can come to with it all is to keep trying to do the small things with great love. Bring as much good and light into every corner of each day.  Thankful for the team around me working so hard to keep making the bandages and bring the healing.  @dzaverl @mogiewav @dannicecelia

Noble things coming soon… 🕊️

That mānuka scent… it evokes such strong memories for me. The smell of wax too, and propolis. A childhood filled with those smells on skin, clothing.. and around the home. It’s fascinating to me to hear how people new to mānuka describe it with no childhood construct or memory around it! 

I have been studying scent recently, both from an allergen and a receptor perspective. Did you know that scent is the only fully developed sense a fetus has in the womb?  It’s the one that is the most developed in a child through the age of around 10 when sight takes over. And because “smell and emotion are stored as one memory,” childhood tends to be the period in which you create “the basis for smells you will like and hate for the rest of your life.”

Fascinating area. I’ve always had a really sensitive nose, and seem to have passed that down to Deo who has one of the strongest reactions to scent I’ve ever seen. Fun test… give your child scents to smell and ask them what color they feel. Most people actually tend to smell IN color… 

You’ll probably find they associate citrus-flavored mandarin with the colors orange, yellow, and green. When smelling vetiver, a grassy scent they will envisage green and brown. Then ask them what color YOU smell like… lol - and be prepared for some fun answers : )

Advent has been a blur this year. Christmas is fast approaching and it feels like there aren’t enough lists or planners to contain all the things on the go. 

The world does seem to shout “be more”, “do more” especially and ironically loud at this season… taking a moment to pause, reflect and find quiet places is a challenge.

Filled with huge amounts of gratitude for all that 2023 has been, but also very ready for a little rest - 3 days till NZ! 

📸 Sneak peak of one quiet moment in an upcoming project that is so far proving to be far more energetic than this would reflect! 🐾🐕😅 @lightbyiris @lolomakeup thanks for working your magic again!

3 days in Auckland - a beautiful blur. I was born here and spent my early working days under the Sky Tower. Felt full circle watching the lights cycle through with Nova. Our stopover ended rather dramatically with a stomach virus…but managed to sneak in some quick catch ups and cuddles 🇳🇿🫶
2023 you have been all the things 🐝 🙏🏻 🕊️
